stylometry: A fixed cost model is trying to find the best solution in either maxmizing profit or minimizing cost when restricted by fixed costs. In other words, the smallest amount of inputs equals the greatest output. Set covering deals with having hubs covered by inputs. In other words a firestation is set covering because when deciding where to put the fire station it had to be decided what area each station would be responsible for. Therefore the set(area) had to be covered in the most efficient matter in order for the fireman to be able to reach the areas in a short amount of time. The goal in both fixed cost models and set covering is how to be most efficient.
